<br>
The most successful and happy mage is one that works with the group and is open to an exchange of information. I have added to my pet control hotkeys emotes so that there is no confusion for eg:<br>
<br>
/assist soandso (puller / 2ndaary assist)<br>
/em commands his pet to KEEEL %t<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
This will take any confusion away from which MoB you actually sent your pet in to attack.<br>
<br>
Another thing I do is assist off of a secondary assist person if there is one. The reason for this is simple on a multi pull the primary puller will see tone target aggro him and then that MoB brings adds. Then once the MoBs show up everyone there jumps on the most appropriate target. That way you assist off of the person who isn’t pulling but who has normally made and informed threat assessment. Also realize that if there are a bunch of mobs around if your pet gets hit on the way to the target then all bets are off and you have to crack the control leash. <br>
